.TH "vmw_validation_preload_bo" 9 "vmw_validation_preload_bo" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_validation_preload_bo \- Preload the validation memory allocator for a call to vmw_validation_add_bo().
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_validation_preload_bo
.BI "(struct vmw_validation_context *ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
Pointer to the validation context.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Iff this function returns successfully, the next call to
\fBvmw_validation_add_bo\fP is guaranteed not to sleep. An error is not fatal
but voids the guarantee.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, -EINVAL otherwise.
